{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"GzngmIfl5WheSbjR3ZxKq","title":"Lecture 20","desc":"","updated":1637727504266,"created":1637727504266,"custom":{},"fname":"courses.Semester 5.Identity and Behaviour.Lecture 20","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"9d9273020cf3ea11723404a6fcab6d2e","links":[],"anchors":{"mbo-self-efficacy-theory-and-expectancy-theory":{"type":"header","text":"MBO, Self-Efficacy theory and Expectancy theory","value":"mbo-self-efficacy-theory-and-expectancy-theory","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"management-by-objectives-mbo":{"type":"header","text":"Management by Objectives (MBO)","value":"management-by-objectives-mbo","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2},"self-efficacy-theory":{"type":"header","text":"Self-Efficacy theory","value":"self-efficacy-theory","line":15,"column":0,"depth":2},"expectancy-theory":{"type":"header","text":"Expectancy theory","value":"expectancy-theory","line":35,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"elcUWYUkVJfjM5NLR8toR","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"lecture-20\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#lecture-20\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Lecture 20</h1>\n<h1 id=\"mbo-self-efficacy-theory-and-expectancy-theory\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#mbo-self-efficacy-theory-and-expectancy-theory\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>MBO, Self-Efficacy theory and Expectancy theory</h1>\n<h2 id=\"management-by-objectives-mbo\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#management-by-objectives-mbo\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Management by Objectives (MBO)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>A program that encompasses specific gials, participatively set, for an explicit time period, with feedback on goal progress.</li>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2021-11-24-09-54-15.png\"></li>\n<li>Can work both top-down or bottom-up approaches.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"self-efficacy-theory\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#self-efficacy-theory\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Self-Efficacy theory</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>An individual's <strong>belief</strong> that <strong>he or she is capable</strong> of performing a task.</li>\n<li>Part of SLT.</li>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2021-11-24-09-57-59.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2021-11-24-09-58-51.png\"></li>\n<li>Increasing Self-Efficacy\n<ul>\n<li>Enactive mastery\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Gaining relevant experience</strong> with the task or job.</li>\n<li>If you didi it in past, you can do it now or in future also.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Vicarious modeling\n<ul>\n<li>Becoming more confident when you see someone else soing the task.</li>\n<li>Condition is that the person should have similar skillset or qualities.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Verbal persuasion\n<ul>\n<li>When someone convinces you about your ability to perform the task.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Arousal\n<ul>\n<li>When you are in an energized state, you feel that you can also perform the task.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>How to increase self-efficacy in others?\n<ul>\n<li>Self-fulfilling prophecy (Pygmalion effect)</li>\n<li><strong>Expectation, shape and behaviour.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"expectancy-theory\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#expectancy-theory\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Expectancy theory</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2021-11-24-10-06-46.png\"></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"GL4YoVrbDUHLnf946YtXV","title":"Curated Notes","desc":"","updated":1630150480330,"created":1629975412335,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"59326d373